text = "It consists of two wheels: one rotates around an axis and the other translate
along this same axis. It is this movement that removes the tegument.

These two wheels are visible on the open model right next to this one.

It is possible to adjust the rotation speed of the first wheel and the distance
between the two wheels depending on the type of seed and the quantity
to be processed.

With other machines, the dehulling process is carried out using a pair of 
shearing rollers. The product is then sorted by sieving.

It is used in particular for buckwheat and millet."
